&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;With over 30 years of experience in the acquisition, development, rehabilitation, and management of apartment communities across the Western United States, we are a trusted partner in the property management industry. At MG Properties, we focus on enriching lives – physically in our community buildings, philanthropically through giving back to our local communities, and through development and growth of our employees.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Central Service Support Administrator (CSSA) provides administrative and project support to the Central Service Department.. They may be directly responsible for performing a variety of office administrative and reporting functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is a fully onsite role at the MG Properties Corporate Office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Primary Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process regularly scheduled documents such as monthly reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle a large volume of department mailings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and report monthly mailings of legal notices and demands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assists with reporting schedules and calendars.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Operations Suite office supplies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in organizing seminars, training courses and department events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconcile department invoices, credit cards and expense reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting in preparation and dissemination of communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with special projects, which may include planning and coordinating presentations, and department events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge, Experience, Educational Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High school diploma/GED required. Associate or bachelor’s degree preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Two to three years of administrative experience. Real Estate or property management experience preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solution oriented with high level reasoning, creativity, and strategic thinking ability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of office management systems and procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MS Office and English proficiency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Skills, Abilities, and Characteristics Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Computer savvy and good with new technology and software’s&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent attention to detail is a requirement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to cross check ones work multiple times to reduce errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be able to handle a large volume of work, accurately and quickly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A very flexible attitude is a must. Person to be flexible several times a day to switch between various roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidate must possess a great “can-do” attitude&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-initiator and ability to do tasks with little supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Time Management skills and ability to prioritize and meet deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to collaborate effectively with a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding organizational skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation and Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$20-$22/hour DOE&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company profit sharing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accrues 10 days Paid time off per year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10 Paid Holidays and 2 Paid Personal Days per year&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Sick Time dependent on location of position&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401K with employer match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical, Dental, Vision, Employee Assistance Program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Life Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
